    "description": "Kimoto Co., Ltd. engages in the manufacture and sale of various film and paper products in Japan and internationally. It offers a range of films, including hard coat films for membrane switches; hard coat, optical, shatter-proof, decorative, and conductive films; formable hard-coated films; light diffusion and reflection films; printed circuit board films; light-blocking films; pressure-sensitive adhesive films for industrial use; molding films; display inkjet films; transfer films; antibacterial and antiviral films; environmentally friendly films; CAD inkjet films; window films; and functional liquid films. The company also provides a variety of services, such as editing and processing of point cloud data, creation of 3D modeling data, geospatial information data creation, digital image data processing, spatial photography, software and system development, manufacturing DX solution proposals, AR/VR/MR services, digital twin system construction, data cloud management services, data storage services, online quotation services, work style reform consulting, manufacturing DX consulting, and book publishing. In addition, it is involved in the planning, design, and development of communication tools. Furthermore, the company offers spatial information and image editing/system development services for 3D point cloud data acquired from laser surveying, as well as 2D map data used for surveys and land registration. The company is also involved in the development and sale of software, production and sale of agricultural products, and consulting businesses. Kimoto Co., Ltd. was founded in 1949 and is headquartered in Inabe, Japan."
